### Books REST API — Chapter 11 (JWT auth)
### Use VS Code "REST Client" or import into Postman.
###
### Tip: paste the value of access_token from /auth/login into the
### @token variable below to get one-click auth on every protected call.

@host  = http://localhost:8000
@token = eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJib29rcy1hcGkiLCJzdWIiOjIsImlhdCI6MTc4MjEyMjU4NywiZXhwIjoxNzgyMTI2MTg3LCJyb2xlIjoibWVtYmVyIiwiZW1haWwiOiJtZW1iZXJAYm9va3MudGVzdCJ9.2f604Q63NGO_0OiyI87Pe-Je059If0-HZ3InTqnX6Y0

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Public — anyone can call
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Health
GET {{host}}/

### List books (public)
GET {{host}}/api/books

### Show one book (public)
GET {{host}}/api/books/1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Register a new user
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Register
POST {{host}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name":     "Hilang Reader",
  "email":    "hilang@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Login (returns the JWT)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Login as the seeded admin
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email":    "admin@books.test",
  "password": "password"
}

### Login as the seeded member
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email":    "member@books.test",
  "password": "password"
}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. Protected calls — copy access_token above into @token
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Current user
GET {{host}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create a book (must be authenticated)
POST {{host}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title":  "Refactoring",
  "author": "Martin Fowler",
  "year":   2018,
  "genre":  "Software Engineering"
}

### Update a book (member or admin)
PUT {{host}}/api/books/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "year":  2009,
  "genre": "Software Craftsmanship"
}

### Delete a book (admin only — members get 403)
DELETE {{host}}/api/books/2
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# 5. Negative cases — verify the guards work
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### Wrong password (expect 401)
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "admin@books.test", "password": "wrong" }

### Missing token (expect 401)
POST {{host}}/api/books
Content-Type: application/json

{ "title": "Should fail", "author": "Nobody", "year": 2024 }

### Tampered token (expect 401)
GET {{host}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.tampered.signature
